BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 5.092 of the Revised Code be 4
enacted to read as follows: 5
Sec. 5.092. (A) The Cleveland metroparks system is 6
declared to be "Ohio's Emerald Necklace" for all of the 7
following reasons: 8
(1) To acknowledge the system as a nationally recognized 9
network of natural spaces, trails, waterways, and recreational 10
amenities spanning more than twenty-five thousand acres across 11
northeast Ohio; 12
(2) To honor the system's encircling layout of green 13
spaces that preserve natural beauty and provide public access to 14
nature, outdoor recreation, and environmental education; 15
(3) In recognition of the system's significant 16
contribution to the quality of life, public health, ecological 17
resilience, and tourism in northeast Ohio; 18
(4) In appreciation of the system, which serves over 19

